{{WikiProject Military history|class=C|B1=n|B2=y|B3=y|B4=y|B5=y|AFV=yes|Korean=yes}} == Orphaned references in [[:Tanks of North Korea]] == I check pages listed in [[:Category:Pages with incorrect ref formatting]] to try to fix reference errors. One of the things I do is look for content for [[User:AnomieBOT/docs/OrphanReferenceFixer|orphaned references]] in wikilinked articles. I have found content for some of [[:Tanks of North Korea]]'s orphans, the problem is that I found more than one version. I can't determine which (if any) is correct for ''this'' article, so I am asking for a sentient editor to look it over and copy the correct ref content into this article. Reference named "SIPRI":
  • From [[ZSU-57-2]]: [http://armstrade.sipri.org/arms_trade/trade_register.php SIPRI Arms Transfers Database]. Armstrade.sipri.org. Retrieved on 14 September 2011.
  • From [[Tanks in the Soviet Union]]: {{cite web|url=http://armstrade.sipri.org/arms_trade/trade_register.php|title=Trade Registers|work=sipri.org|accessdate=9 December 2014}}
  • From [[List of main battle tanks by country]]: [http://armstrade.sipri.org/arms_trade/trade_register.php SIPRI Arms Transfers Database]
  • From [[Magach]]: {{Citation | contribution = Trade register | contribution-url = http://armstrade.sipri.org/armstrade/page/trade_register.php | title = Arms trade | publisher = Sipri}}.
  • From [[PT-76]]: {{cite web|url=http://armstrade.sipri.org/arms_trade/trade_register.php|title=SIPRI Arms Transfers Database|publisher=|accessdate=15 November 2014}}

  • From [[FV101 Scorpion]]: {{cite web|publisher=[[Jane's Information Group]]|title=Scorpion|url=http://www.janes.com/defence/land_forces/supplement/lav/lav_scorpion.shtml |accessdate=2009-01-11}}
  • From [[T-14 Armata]]: {{cite web|url=http://www.janes.com/article/51469/russia-s-armour-revolution|title=Russia's armour revolution|website=Jane's 360}}
  • From [[Type 59 tank]]: {{cite book|title=Jane's Armour and Artillery 2005-2006|author=Christopher F Foss.}}
  • From [[T-64]]: {{cite web|url=http://www.janes.com/article/40139/ukraine-captures-russian-t-64-mbt-near-donetsk|title=Ukraine captures 'Russian' T-64 MBT near Donetsk - IHS Jane's 360|publisher=janes.com|accessdate=25 October 2014}}
  • From [[Al-Khalid tank]]: {{cite web|url=http://www.janes.com/defence/news/jdw/jdw060313_1_n.shtml|title=Saudi Arabia to trial Al Khalid MBT|author=Farhan Bokhari|date=13 March 2006|publisher=[[Jane's Information Group]] | archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20090503164925/http://janes.com/defence/news/jdw/jdw060313_1_n.shtml | archivedate=1 October 2013}}
